{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013Vx13Vsbe6LZcEQuATwqHZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The CockroachDB cluster is fully operational. Here's a summary of what was done and why:\n\n**Root Cause:** The 3 nodes were all running with `--join` flags pointing to each other, waiting in a mutual bootstrap deadlock — none of them could form the cluster without an explicit initialization command. This is expected CockroachDB behavior: peers can discover each other via `--join`, but someone must fire `cockroach init` to actually bootstrap the Raft consensus group.\n\n**Fix:** Ran `cockroach init --insecure --host=localhost:26257` from `crdb-cluster-0`. This bootstrapped the cluster on node 0, after which nodes 1 and 2 joined automatically via the `--join` list they were already configured with.\n\n**Final State:**\n- All 3 pods: `1/1 Running` (readiness probe passing)\n- All 3 nodes: `is_available=true`, `is_live=true`\n- SQL connections accepted on port 26257 (public service `crdb-cluster-public` also available)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":753,"cache_read_input_tokens":41556,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":753},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f555f9da-80f3-490b-a2e4-f5fef0ad1c65","uuid":"154f69b0-e58f-49b8-84cd-3a62299d139c","request_id":"req_011CcRBupPikMh3G4B595ej9"}
